  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all model inputs, yielding probability distributions for the hemolysis index at each of five flow-speed operating points. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels under the MRL 5 framework. Decision: Accepted.",
