    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels for MRL 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification across all model inputs confirms that the 95th-percentile hemolysis index prediction remains below the clinical threshold at each of the five COU operating points. Validation activities are directly relevant to the COU geometry and operating conditions, with MAPE of 9.7% and NIA of 0.93. The credibility evidence package is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the Class III VAD device.",
